s, in a most personal fashion, shared with these scholars his ideological struggle between his love for Torah study and “hokhmah” (philosophy, wisdom). This Grand Epistle reveals much about this towering figure and provides a moving portrait of him during his last decade.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aHebrew languagexProsodic analysis. 0aJewish scholarszFrancezLunelvCorrespondence. 0aProsodic analysis (Linguistics). 0aResponsay1040-1600. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Sacred Writings.2bisacsh  aCode of Jewish Law.  aEpistolary compositions.  aHokhmah.  aIggeret.  aLate Middle Ages.  aMaimonides.  aMiddle Ages.  aMishneh Torah.  aScholars of Lunel.  aSephardic poetic style.  aTanakh.  aTorah.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311068819108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies ASPz978311071683240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618119629zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781618119629423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781618119629/original  a978-3-11-068819-1  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-071683-2  Religious Studies ASP  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK